institutionalize the approved lessons.

.why = crystallize lessons into reusable briefs or upgrade handoffs for future travelers.

---

## how to institutionalize

### step 1: review approved lessons

read 7.reflection.yield.md and identify lessons with human approval:

| lesson | type | approved | action |
|--------|------|----------|--------|
| {name} | rule/howto/handoff | yes/no | create brief / skip |

only institutionalize lessons that received human approval.

### step 2: determine brief type

| if the lesson... | then create... | example |
|------------------|----------------|---------|
| forbids a pattern | `rule.forbid.*.md` | rule.forbid.shared-mutable-state.md |
| requires a pattern | `rule.require.*.md` | rule.require.test-isolation.md |
| teaches a technique | `howto.*.md` | howto.mock-timers-safely.md |
| needs infra change | `handoff.*.md` | handoff.ci-parallel-isolation.md |

### step 3: write the brief

for rules and howtos, use this structure:

```markdown
# {title}

## .what
{one line description}

## .why
{what problem this solves, what flakes this prevents}

## .pattern
{the concrete pattern to follow}

## .examples
### good
{code example that follows the pattern}

### bad
{code example that violates the pattern}

## .source
from cicd.deflake reflection on {date}
```

for handoffs, use this structure:

```markdown
# handoff: {title}

## .what
{what needs to change}

## .why
{root cause this addresses}

## .proposed fix
{concrete steps to implement}

## .files to modify
- path/to/file.ts
- .github/workflows/test.yml

## .validation
{how to verify the fix worked}

## .source
from cicd.deflake reflection on {date}
```

### step 4: commit each brief

```sh
# stage the brief
git add .agent/repo=.this/role=any/briefs/{brief-name}.md

# commit with traceable message
git commit -m "fix(briefs): add {brief-name} from cicd.deflake reflection

- institutionalizes lesson from deflake cycle on {date}
- prevents: {what flake pattern this prevents}"
```

